    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-13T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-13T05:00:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 U.S.S.R./32: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BWC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-13T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 13, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 13—12:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Your telegram No. 42, April 12, 1 p.m. <persName corresp="#p_REV1"
                        >Rubinin</persName>’s trip ostensibly is to familiarize himself with the
                    United States. His real purpose is to give <persName corresp="#p_TAA1"
                        >Troyanovsky</persName> an intimate view of <persName corresp="#p_LMM1"
                        >Litvinov</persName>’s position with regard to the matter of debts and
                    claims and to bring back to Moscow first-hand information as to the position of
                    the Government of the United States.</p>
                <p>I am informed unofficially but I think reliably that <persName corresp="#p_TAA1"
                        >Troyanovsky</persName> has reported that he is in a helpless position being
                    unable successfully to interpret the assurances which <persName
                        corresp="#p_LMM1">Litvinov</persName> gave in Washington or to contest the
                    position taken by the Department.</p>
                <p>I feel sure that <persName corresp="#p_REV1">Rubinin</persName> has not been
                    empowered to enter into any negotiations but merely to give and receive
                    information. Nevertheless I attach great importance to his receiving a swift
                    impact.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
